Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 12:46:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patch 0896: vercel.json - drop Render proxy entirely

User report: SPECIAL_SITUATIONS / WATCHLIST_PULSE / UPCOMING_EARNINGS /
TOP_MOVERS all empty on home, but direct curl on every endpoint
returns 200 with real data:
  /api/v1/special-situations/feed     179 events
  /api/v1/earnings/calendar?days=14   1170 entries
  /api/v1/calendar?days=14            17 entries
  /api/v1/super-investor-flow         rows
  /api/market/intelligence            structured response
  /api/market/quotes?market=india     200 OK (8.8s first hit)

Backend healthy. So the home page is timing out client-side. Two
contributing factors:

1. /api/market/quotes was 8.8s on cold start (Render sleep + warm-up).
   Home pages 8s news-enrichment budget cant accommodate that.
2. My 0890 vercel.json added 20+ self-rewrites that slow Vercels
   edge-routing layer. Vercel evaluates rewrites top-to-bottom per
   request; 20+ entries with regex patterns adds measurable latency.

Verified all 22 /api/v1/* namespaces have Next.js route files (every
folder under src/app/api/v1/). The Render proxy is dead code: no
endpoint actually lives only on Render. The next.config.js comment
the original author wrote explicitly said
  "No rewrite on Vercel - Next.js API routes serve /api/v1/* natively"
- but vercel.json had a catch-all proxy contradicting that. 0890 fixed
the news-india symptom by adding passthroughs around the proxy; 0896
fixes the cause by deleting the proxy.

Net: empty rewrites array. Vercel skips the rewrite layer entirely
for /api/v1/*, Next.js file-based routes serve every request directly,
edge-routing latency drops, home page client-side fetches no longer
time out on cold start of a dead proxy.
